<!-- 1.4.14 -->
<div class='toload definition'>
<p><span class='envidentifier'>Definition 1.4.14</span>
If $\G$ is an ample Hausdorff groupoid, we denote by $\mathbf{KB}(\G)$ the semigroup of compact-open bisections of $\G$, and call it the <em>ample semigroup</em> of $\G$.
</p>
</div>